posts.name: jls667
posts.cooked: I am using YAGSL to program my swerve drive. To do this, setup code is put under a directory called “swerve.” Pathplanner uses a directory “pathplanner.” My program is setting the filesystem to “swerve.” I think that is why my autonomous program is not working. What are other teams doing so the software finds the autonomous files and the swerve yagsl config files?

posts.name: Emre
posts.cooked: I don’t think that’s the issue, it’s supposed to be that way. Did you add a widget to the SmartDashboard to select the correct autonomous? Are you sure you configured it correctly? Have you created the autonomous routine?

posts.name: jls667
posts.cooked: My problem is probably some other issue. I can put autonomous  options on the Smartdashboard. Then it must be how my program deals with the autonomous files. I thought I used the default code from the YAGSL docs to handle Pathplanner.

posts.name: allison zhang
posts.cooked: In what way are your autos not working?

posts.name: allison zhang
posts.cooked: Could you send your code here? I don’t believe this would be a problem with YAGSL , as we did not need to touch the example swerve code.
